#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:0.5"
msgid "51. Surāpānasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.51\">Monks’ Confession 51: the training rule on "
"drinking alcoholic drinks</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā cetiyesu cārikaṃ caramāno yena bhaddavatikā "
"tena pāyāsi."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.51.1\""
">Bu-Pc.51.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.382\">BD.2.382</a><a class"
"=\"wt-pa\">1018</a>At one time the Buddha was wandering in the country of "
"Ceti on his way to Bhaddavatikā."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.2"
msgid ""
"Addasaṃsu kho gopālakā pasupālakā kassakā pathāvino bhagavantaṃ dūratova "
"āgacchantaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A number of cow-herds, shepherds, farmers, and travelers saw the Master "
"coming."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.3"
msgid "Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "And they said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.4"
msgid "“mā kho, bhante, bhagavā ambatitthaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, don’t go to Ambatittha."

#. VAR: āsiviso → āsīviso (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.5"
msgid ""
"Ambatitthe, bhante, jaṭilassa assame nāgo paṭivasati iddhimā āsiviso "
"ghoraviso."
msgstr ""
"There’s a terribly poisonous dragon with supernormal powers there, in the "
"hermitage of a dreadlocked ascetic."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.6"
msgid "So bhagavantaṃ mā viheṭhesī”ti."
msgstr "Don’t let it harm you, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā tuṇhī ahosi."
msgstr "The Master remained silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.8"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe …"
msgstr "They repeated what they had said a second and"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.9"
msgid ""
"tatiyampi kho gopālakā pasupālakā kassakā pathāvino bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and a third time,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.10"
msgid "“mā kho, bhante, bhagavā ambatitthaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.11"
msgid ""
"Ambatitthe, bhante, jaṭilassa assame nāgo paṭivasati iddhimā āsiviso "
"ghoraviso."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.12"
msgid "So bhagavantaṃ mā viheṭhesī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.13"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho bhagavā tuṇhī ahosi."
msgstr "but the Master still remained silent."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli4.109
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.14"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena bhaddavatikā tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"<a class=\"wt-pa\">1019</a> The Master then continued on to Bhaddavatikā,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.15"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā bhaddavatikāyaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""
"and he <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.109\">Vin.4.109</a> stayed "
"there.</p>"

#. VAR: ambatitthassa → amba­tittha­kassa (bj, pts1) | ambatitthaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.16"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāgato yena ambatitthassa jaṭilassa assamo tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"<p>Just then Venerable Sāgata went to the hermitage of that dreadlocked "
"ascetic"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.17"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā agyāgāraṃ pavisitvā tiṇasanthārakaṃ paññapetvā nisīdi "
"pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"and entered his fire hut. After preparing a straw-mat, he sat down, crossed "
"his legs, <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.383\">BD.2.383</a> straightened "
"his body, and established mindfulness in front of him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.18"
msgid "Addasā kho so nāgo āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ paviṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "Seeing that Sāgata had entered the fire hut,"

#. VAR: padhūpāyi → padhūpāsi (s1-3, pts1, mr) 
#. VAR: Disvāna dummano → dukkhī dummano (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.19"
msgid "Disvāna dummano padhūpāyi."
msgstr "the dragon was upset and emitted smoke."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.20"
msgid "Āyasmāpi sāgato padhūpāyi."
msgstr "Sāgata, too, emitted smoke."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.21"
msgid "Atha kho so nāgo makkhaṃ asahamāno pajjali."
msgstr "The dragon was not able to contain his rage and emitted flames."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.22"
msgid "Āyasmāpi sāgato tejodhātuṃ samāpajjitvā pajjali."
msgstr "Sāgata entered the fire element and he, too, emitted flames."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.23"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāgato tassa nāgassa tejasā tejaṃ pariyādiyitvā yena "
"bhaddavatikā tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"Then, after conquering fire with fire, Sāgata went to Bhaddavatikā.\n"
"Soon afterwards the lay followers at Kosambī heard that Sāgata had fought "
"the Ambatittha dragon.</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.24"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā bhaddavatikāyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena kosambī tena "
"cārikaṃ pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"<p>After staying at Bhaddavatikā for as long as he liked, the Master set out "
"wandering towards Kosambī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.25"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho kosambikā upāsakā—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.26"
msgid "“ayyo kira sāgato ambatitthikena nāgena saddhiṃ saṅgāmesī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.27"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena kosambī tadavasari."
msgstr "<a class=\"wt-pa\">1020</a> When he arrived,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.28"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kosambikā upāsakā bhagavato paccuggamanaṃ karitvā yenāyasmā sāgato "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"the lay followers there received him.</p> <p>After receiving the Master, the "
"lay followers went to see Sāgata. "

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.29"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu."
msgstr "They bowed, stood to one side,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.30"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho kosambikā upāsakā āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.31"
msgid "“kiṃ, bhante, ayyānaṃ dullabhañca manāpañca, kiṃ paṭiyādemā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, what may we prepare for you that is hard to obtain yet "
"pleasant?”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.32"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kosambike upāsake etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "<p>The monks from the group of six replied,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.33"
msgid ""
"“atthāvuso, kāpotikā nāma pasannā bhikkhūnaṃ dullabhā ca manāpā ca, taṃ "
"paṭiyādethā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There’s a liquor called Kāpotikā, which is hard for the monks to get, yet "
"pleasant. Prepare that.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.34"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kosambikā upāsakā ghare ghare kāpotikaṃ pasannaṃ paṭiyādetvā "
"āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭhaṃ disvāna āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr ""
"<p>And the lay followers prepared <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.384\""
">BD.2.384</a> Kāpotikā liquor in house after house. Then, when they saw that "
"Sāgata had entered the town for alms, they said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.35"
msgid ""
"“pivatu, bhante, ayyo sāgato kāpotikaṃ pasannaṃ, pivatu, bhante, ayyo sāgato "
"kāpotikaṃ pasannan”ti."
msgstr "“Drink, Venerable, drink the Kāpotikā liquor.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.36"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāgato ghare ghare kāpotikaṃ pasannaṃ pivitvā nagaramhā "
"nikkhamanto nagaradvāre paripati."
msgstr ""
"Sāgata drank that liquor in house after house, and as he was leaving town, "
"he collapsed at the town gate.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, pts-vp-pli4.110
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.37"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ nagaramhā nikkhamanto addasa "
"āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ nagaradvāre paripatantaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1021</a>Just then the Master, together with a number "
"of monks, was also leaving town, and he saw Sāgata collapsed at the town "
"gate."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.38"
msgid "Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "He said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.39"
msgid "“gaṇhatha, bhikkhave, sāgatan”ti."
msgstr "“Monks, pick up Sāgata.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.40"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissuṇitvā āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ "
"ārāmaṃ netvā yena bhagavā tena sīsaṃ katvā nipātesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Saying, “Yes, Master,” they led him to the monastery, where they put him "
"down with his head towards the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.41"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāgato parivattitvā yena bhagavā tena pāde karitvā seyyaṃ "
"kappesi."
msgstr "But Sāgata turned around, pointing his feet towards the Master.</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.42"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "<p>The Master said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.43"
msgid "“nanu, bhikkhave, pubbe sāgato tathāgate sagāravo ahosi sappatisso”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Previously, monks, wasn’t Sāgata respectful and <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\""
"Vin.4.110\">Vin.4.110</a> deferential towards the Buddha?”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.44"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "<p>“Yes, Venerable Sir.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.45"
msgid ""
"“Api nu kho, bhikkhave, sāgato etarahi tathāgate sagāravo sappatisso”ti?"
msgstr "<p>“But is he now respectful and deferential towards the Buddha?”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.46"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "<p>“Certainly not, Venerable Sir.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.47"
msgid "“Nanu, bhikkhave, sāgato ambatitthikena nāgena saddhiṃ saṅgāmesī”ti?"
msgstr "<p>“Just recently, didn’t Sāgata fight with the Ambatittha dragon?”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.48"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "<p>“Yes, Venerable Sir.”</p>"

#. VAR: pahoti nāgena → deḍḍhubhenāpi (bj) | deḍḍubhenapi (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.49"
msgid ""
"“Api nu kho, bhikkhave, sāgato etarahi pahoti nāgena saddhiṃ saṅgāmetun”ti?"
msgstr "<p>“Would he now be able to fight with a dragon?”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.50"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "<p>“Certainly not, Venerable Sir.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.51"
msgid "“Api nu kho, bhikkhave, taṃ pātabbaṃ yaṃ pivitvā visaññī assā”ti?"
msgstr "<p>“So, monks, should one drink that which makes one senseless?”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.52"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "<p>“Certainly not, Venerable Sir.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.53"
msgid ""
"“Ananucchavikaṃ, bhikkhave, sāgatassa ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ "
"akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<p>“It’s not suitable, monks, it’s not proper for Sāgata, it’s not worthy of "
"an ascetic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.54"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, sāgato majjaṃ pivissati."
msgstr ""
"How can <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.385\">BD.2.385</a> Sāgata drink "
"alcoholic drinks?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.55"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.56"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc5
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:1.57"
msgid "“Surāmerayapāne pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2><p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1022</a>‘If a monk drinks this or that kind of alcoholic drink, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.1.1"
msgid "Surā nāma"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.51.2\"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-"
"Pc.51.2.1\">Bu-Pc.51.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1023</a><term>This […] kind "
"of alcoholic drink</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.1.2"
msgid "piṭṭhasurā pūvasurā odanasurā kiṇṇapakkhittā sambhārasaṃyuttā."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>alcoholic drinks made from flour, alcoholic drinks made from "
"biscuits, alcoholics drink made from rice, those with yeast added, those "
"made from a combination of ingredients.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.1.3"
msgid "Merayo nāma"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1024</a><term>That kind of alcoholic drink</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.1.4"
msgid "pupphāsavo phalāsavo madhvāsavo guḷāsavo sambhārasaṃyutto."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>alcoholic drinks made from flowers, alcoholic drinks made from fruit, "
"alcoholic drinks made from honey, alcoholic drinks made from sugar, those "
"made from a combination of ingredients.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.1.5"
msgid "Piveyyāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1025</a><term>Drinks</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.1.6"
msgid "antamaso kusaggenapi pivati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if he drinks even the amount on the tip of a blade of grass, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.2.1"
msgid "Majje majjasaññī pivati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.51.2.2\">Bu-Pc.51.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1026</a>If it is an alcoholic drink, and he perceives it as alcoholic, and "
"he drinks it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.2.2"
msgid "Majje vematiko pivati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an alcoholic drink, but he is unsure if it is, and he drinks it, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.2.3"
msgid "Majje amajjasaññī pivati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an alcoholic drink, but he does not perceive it as alcoholic, and "
"he drinks it, he commits an offense entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.2.4"
msgid "Amajje majjasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1027</a>If it is not an alcoholic drink, but he "
"perceives it as alcoholic, <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.386\""
">BD.2.386</a> he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.2.5"
msgid "Amajje vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not an alcoholic drink, but he is unsure of it, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.2.6"
msgid "Amajje amajjasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is not an alcoholic drink, and he does not perceive it as alcoholic, "
"there is no offense.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.51.2."
"3\">Bu-Pc.51.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1028</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.3.2"
msgid ""
"amajjañca hoti majjavaṇṇaṃ majjagandhaṃ majjarasaṃ taṃ pivati, sūpasampāke, "
"maṃsasampāke, telasampāke, āmalakaphāṇite, amajjaṃ ariṭṭhaṃ pivati, "
"ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if it is not an alcoholic drink, but it has the color of an alcoholic drink, "
"the smell of an alcoholic drink, or the taste of an alcoholic drink, and he "
"drinks that; if it is cooked in a bean curry; if it is cooked with meat; if "
"it is cooked with oil; if it is in sugar with emblic myrobalan; if he drinks "
"a drink that is normally alcoholic, but which is actually without alcohol; "
"if he is insane; if he is the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc51:2.3.3"
msgid "Surāpānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1029</a>The first rule, the "
"training rule on drinking alcoholic drinks, is finished.</p>"
